dismissalComment.html: Rasel cleans him up with a slower one. His special- the off cutter. Masakadza shaped for the big slog across the line but was beaten by the lack of pace. Fine innings comes to an end. A very good partnership with Taylor.

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor run out (Raqibul Hasan/†Mushfiqur Rahim) 94 (103b 2x4 1x6 116m) SR: 91.26

dismissalComment.html: Taylor is run out, going for the second run. It was pushed towards long-off and Chigumbura pushed for the second run. Taylor rushed across and even tried to dive into the crease but the throw  was accurate and fast and Rahim did the rest.  A very fine knock from Taylor comes to an end.
And he is gone now. He tries to slog sweep from outside off stump but gets a leading edge and presents a dolly to short third-man fielder. Handy little innings, though.
Shakib gets one more wicket. Another slog sweep attempted, another edge, and it's caught at midwicket

Wow! what a delivery. Don't blame Sibanda for edging it. It curved away late from a good length and clipped the outer edge as Sibanda pushed at it; he had to play at it. It did just enough to get the edge. There is no use getting dramatic big movement and missing the bat. Perfect delivery.
What a soft dismissal. Vermeulen, who was looking so good, is gone. It was full and slipping to the legs, it could have been on driven anywhere but Vermeulen flicked it straight to short midwicket.

dismissalText.commentary: Charles Coventry run out (Mehrab Hossain jnr/†Mushfiqur Rahim) 22 (20b 3x4 1x6 31m) SR: 110

dismissalComment.html: What a mess. What terrible misunderstanding between the two. It was flicked past square leg and the fielder (Mehrab) ran in from deep square leg. Clearly they had to stop at a single as they never seemed sure of the second. But they turned for the second run, hesitated mid-way, tried to carry on forward but too late folks. The throw was accurate and Rahim whips off the bails in glee. Gone!

dismissalText.commentary: Raqibul Hasan b Masakadza 78 (83b 4x4 2x6 113m) SR: 93.97

dismissalComment.html: Masakadza ends Raqibul's superb resistance. It was full and straight, Raqibul tried to repeat the six from the earlier over as he went for another big swing towards midwicket  but couldn't get any wood on leather. Clatter!

dismissalText.commentary: Mahbubul Alam c Vermeulen b Mupariwa 59 (43b 2x4 3x6 49m) SR: 137.2

dismissalComment.html: Rock the baby Mupariwa! He produces another edge as the batsman goes for a similar slog and this time it settles down safely at backward point. Zimbabwe have won their first game of the series. Remember, Bangladesh have already won two. Game on now.

image.caption: Ray Price
image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalComment.html: Price gets a wicket for his fine bowling. Again, tossed up, loopy delivery luring Rahim down the track and he hit it straight down to long-on. Reward for some good bowling. Five down now and tottering ...
Price takes out another. The wheels are coming off. It was another nice tempting loopy flighted delivery, he went down the track but ended up chipping it straight to long-off.

Price cleans him up with the arm-ball. He was clueless as he went back and stabbed outside the line of the ball. The off stump was pegged back and Zimbabwe are just a wicket away from getting their first win of the series.

Mupariwa has struck gold first ball. It was a lovely curving delivery around the off stump, Tamim stabbed it, without moving his feet,  straight to first slip. Mupariwa celebrates as if he is rocking a baby. Memories of Bebeto, Romario from the World Cup football. Here we go. What a start.

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Ashraful combusts spectacularly. He ran down the wicket and tried to slash it over covers but the ball flew off the outside edge straight down to third man. Three down and the Bangladesh boat is rocking. And so is Mupariwa.

commentPostTextItems.html: Hang on for the post-match ceremony.

Shakib: "We didn't bowl well. It was a tough day for us; hopefully we woudl come back in the next game. We didn't start well with the bat. Only 80 runs were needed in the last overs but we didn't have wickets."
Utseya: "The guys managed to come to the party today. Form is temporary, class is permanent. I think our batting can still improve. On that wicket, 350 is a good score."
Man of the Match : Chigumbura: "It was a good innings. The guys upfront did a good job to help me come in and play my game. We have to do well on Sunday to level the series."
That's it from us. Join us on Sunday. Good bye and good luck.
